ExecDesc.value: Microsoft DirectX WAV and AVI File Parsing Code Execution

EngDesc.value: A buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Microsoft DirectX application framework. The vulnerability is due to the way certain DirectX libraries handle specially crafted WAV and AVI files. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by persuading a user to open a specially crafted WAV or AVI file, potentially causing arbitrary code to be injected and executed in the security context of the logged in user.
